BT 1 0 0 1 0 87 Tm -0.10635 Tw 12 TL /F1 9 Tf 0 0 0 rg (In 2016, Li-Huei Tsai's lab at MIT published in ) Tj /F3 9 Tf (Nature) Tj /F1 9 Tf ( that a 40 Hz flickering light reduced amyloid-beta in Alzheimer's model) Tj T* 0 Tw (mice. In 2019, adding 40 Hz audio extended the effect to the hippocampus and reduced tau phosphorylation. In 2024, the) Tj T* (mechanism was identified: 40 Hz sensory stimulation drives VIP interneurons to release vasoactive intestinal peptide,) Tj T* (activating glymphatic clearance of amyloid. An independent Chinese lab replicated the glymphatic result the same year.) Tj T* (Human Phase I/II trials \(PLOS ONE, 2022-2023\) showed significantly reduced hippocampal atrophy, less ventricular) Tj T* (dilation, improved memory, and increased functional connectivity in mild Alzheimer's patients after 3 months of daily 40 Hz) Tj T* (audiovisual stimulation. Two-year follow-up \(2025\) confirmed safety and potential slowing of cognitive decline. A Phase III) Tj T* (pivotal trial \(Cognito Therapeutics\) is currently running.) Tj T* ET
